    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Intruduction'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans SC Black' fontsize='28'>Introduction</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>This time, we present three groups of information from the options data:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>1. Implied volatility curves for different quote dates and expiries, including both the volatility smile and the volatility skew.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>2. For options across different quote dates, the relationship between relative spread and open interest, as well as the relationship between relative spread and volume.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>3.For each expiry, the evolution of the option 25-delta skew over quote dates, so that we can identify points where the skew shows clear jumps.</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='12' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98000' id='11' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans SC Black' fontsize='28'>Introduction</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>This time, we present three groups of information from the options data:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>1. Implied volatility curves for different quote dates and expiries, including both the volatility smile and the volatility skew.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>2. For options across different quote dates, the relationship between relative spread and open interest, as well as the relationship between relative spread and volume.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Noto Sans TC' fontsize='20'>3.For each expiry, the evolution of the option 25-delta skew over quote dates, so that we can identify points where the skew shows clear jumps.</run>
